    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-23T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-23T12:00:00-05:00" n="138"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Germany)/1–645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Secretary of State to the Ambassador in the United
                        Kingdom</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-23T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >January 23, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>502. Referring to the Department’s telegram No. 153, January 6, midnight,<note
                        n="35" xml:id="d138fn35">Not printed; it reported that the agreement for
                        control machinery for Germany had been approved by the Joint Chiefs of Staff
                        and was under consideration by the President (740.00119 Control
                        (Germany)/1–645)</note> the President has now approved the agreement for
                    control machinery for Germany. Accordingly, you are authorized to give formal
                    notification of this Government’s approval of the agreement to your colleagues
                    on EAC.<note n="36" xml:id="d138fn36">In his telegram 848, January 24, 7 p.m.,
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom reported having addressed formal
                        notifications to the British and Soviet Representatives on the European
                        Advisory Commission (740.00119EAC/1–2445)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
